                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "They did not consider any form of inequality as just."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "They ensure that money stays within the same families from one generation to the next."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "Capitalist societies did not do enough to ensure that wealth and power stay in the hands of a few as “a law of the marketplace.”"
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "They did not do enough to limit the meritocratic aspects of capitalist societies."
